Done. Here's the complete Solana integration layer created at `~/bhavana/src/`:

## Files Created

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `lib/constants.ts` | Program ID, RPC endpoint, 3 properties with IDR prices, PDA derivation helpers, `formatIDR()` |
| `lib/program.ts` | `getProgram(wallet)` for transactions, `getReadOnlyProgram()` for reads, loads IDL |
| `lib/WalletProvider.tsx` | Solana wallet adapter provider wrapping Phantom + wallet modal |
| `lib/polyfills.ts` | Buffer polyfill for Solana in the browser |
| `hooks/useProperties.ts` | Fetches all 3 PropertyAccount PDAs — returns on-chain data merged with seed data, handles uninitialized gracefully |
| `hooks/useBuyShares.ts` | Calls `buy_shares` instruction with `idle → pending → confirmed/error` state machine, error messages in Indonesian |
| `hooks/usePortfolio.ts` | Fetches user's SPL token balances across all Bhavana mints, calculates value in IDR + estimated monthly yield |
| `hooks/useDistributeYield.ts` | Admin-only: calls `distribute_yield` per holder, error messages in Indonesian |

## How to Wire Into Your App

```tsx
// main.tsx — add at the top:
import "./lib/polyfills";

// Wrap your app:
import { WalletProvider } from "./lib/WalletProvider";

ReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById("root")!).render(
  <WalletProvider>
    <App />
  </WalletProvider>
);
```

```tsx
// In a component:
import { useProperties } from "./hooks/useProperties";
import { useBuyShares } from "./hooks/useBuyShares";
import { usePortfolio } from "./hooks/usePortfolio";

function PropertyCard({ property }) {
  const { buyShares, status, error } = useBuyShares();

  return (
    <button 
      onClick={() => buyShares(property.seed.name, 1)}
      disabled={status === "pending"}
    >
      {status === "pending" ? "Processing..." : `Beli 1 Share — ${property.priceDisplayIDR}`}
    </button>
  );
}
```

## Next Steps

1. Run `npm install` (adds Solana deps)
2. Add `buffer` to dependencies: `npm install buffer`
3. Build your Anchor program and copy the IDL to `anchor/target/idl/bhavana.json`
4. Import `polyfills.ts` at the top of `main.tsx`
5. Wrap your app in `<WalletProvider>`
6. Use the hooks in your components

Want me to build the actual React components (PropertyCard, Portfolio dashboard, BuyModal) that use these hooks?

